Goal: exhaustively list all meteor software ressources. If anything is missing by all means please add it here! :-)

Other ressources webpages:
- IMO webpage: https://www.imo.net/resources/software/

How to setup a multi-station optical meteor station
- IMO QRicht: https://www.imo.net/resources/software/qricht/

Optical recording and detection of meteors
Windows:
- FreeTure: https://github.com/fripon/freeture
- MetRec: http://www.metrec.org/
- UFOCapture: (not free) http://sonotaco.com/e_index.html

Linux:
- FreeTure: https://github.com/fripon/freeture
- ASGARD: not publicly available (R. Weryk, UWO, Canada): http://meteor.uwo.ca/~weryk/asgard/
- RMS: Croatia Meteor Network: acquisition and detection with Raspberry-pi: https://github.com/CroatianMeteorNetwork/RMS

Radio recording:
- SpectrumLab: http://www.qsl.net/dl4yhf/spectra1.html#download
- Colorgramme: http://radio.meteor.free.fr/


Lunar Flash
- windows: LunarScan: Freeware: http://www.lunarimpacts.com/lunarimpacts_howto.htm


Organizing meteor data, digging into the data:
- R: Veljkovic ; https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/
- python: CMN CMN_binViewer to organize CAMS data: https://github.com/CroatianMeteorNetwork/cmn_binviewer

Meteor database:
- IAU meteor database: http://pallas.astro.amu.edu.pl/~jopek/MDC2007/index.php
- EDMOND: http://www.daa.fmph.uniba.sk/edmond
- IMO Databases: https://www.imo.net/resources/databases/
- SonotaCo: http://sonotaco.jp/doc/SNM/
- CAMS: http://cams.seti.org/
- AMS visual witness: http://www.amsmeteors.org/members/imo_view/browse_events/


Computation of 3D-Trajectory and orbital elements
- Python: FRIPIPE: the FRIPON pipeline: will be made freely pubicly available in early 2018 ; see: www.fripon.org
- C/C++: Metal (R. Weryk, UWO, Canada): not publicly available ; http://meteor.uwo.ca/~weryk/asgard/metal.html
- FreeWare: UFOAnalyzer and UFOOrbit: not open source: http://sonotaco.com/soft/e_index.html

Computation of meteorite fall location and strewn field
- Python: FRIPIPE: the FRIPON pipeline: will be made freely pubicly available in early 2018 ; see: www.fripon.org


Miscalenaous codes:
- Croatia Meteor Network: https://github.com/CroatianMeteorNetwork/CMN-codes
